A 30-year-old motorbike rider has been killed in an accident that occurred before Woodmead, R55 bridge, on Saturday. According to Netcare 911, paramedics attended to the man but unfortunately, he sustained fatal injuries and was declared dead at the scene. Reports from the scene allege that the driver lost control of his bike, hitting the barrier and was thrown off his bike. “The bike was found about 400m down the road at the Buccleuch split. “The exact circumstances surrounding the accident is not yet known,” Netcare 911 said. Metro police were on scene investigating. -TNA Reporter  